data.name: Cilantro Lime Shrimp Rice
data.quickTastyDescription: A zesty and refreshing shrimp dish with a burst of lime and fresh cilantro, served over rice for a satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Rinse the rice under cold water until the water runs clear.
In a pot, combine the rice and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until the rice is cooked and liquid is absorbed.
While the rice cooks, heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add minced garlic to the skillet and cook for about 30 seconds until fragrant.
Add the shrimp to the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook for 3-4 minutes until they turn pink and opaque.
Stir in lime juice and chopped cilantro, cooking for an additional minute.
Serve the shrimp mixture over the cooked rice, garnishing with extra cilantro and lime wedges if desired.
data.detailedName: Zesty Cilantro Lime Shrimp with Rice
